 Lymph nodes that are radioactive, blue, magnetic or palpable are considered SLNs and are resected and submitted for pathological analysis.

 The protocol required that at least 2 SLNs to be resected.

 In all cases a completion axillary lymphadenectomy nodes dissection (ALND) will be performed after SLN biopsy.

