 Sentinel Lymph Node Biopsy With Superparamagnetic Iron Oxide for Breast Cancer Patients After Neoadjuvant Treatment.

@highlight

The purpose of this study is to determine the detection rate and the false negative rate of sentinel lymph node (SLN) by superparamagnetic iron oxide (SPIO) alone or in addition to radioisotope and compared to the standard method (blue and radioisotope) after neoadjuvant chemotherapy in patients with node-positive breast cancer converted to node negative after treatment by ultrasound.

 A randomized controlled trial.

